						<summary>

						<p>Impression received from the Dy. Dir. Arch., Maharashtra, Aurangabad.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It recorded probably a land grant (to a temple ?) with a house and a well. The names of the donor and donee are lost. The five hundred <hi rend="italic">svāmis</hi> of a guild probably from Dēvakadere can be made out. This highly damaged record is in characters of 11th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
